Former Public Protector, Thuli Madonsela says she'd be surprised if the court ruling on lockdown regulations survives the scrutiny of a higher court. The high court in Pretoria has declared levels 3 and 4 unconstitutional and invalid. But Madonsela feels the ruling lacked clarity, accuracy and persuasive reasoning. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former Public Protector Thuli Madonsela says she would be surprised if the court ruling on lockdown regulations survives the scrutiny of a higher court. The High Court in Pretoria has declared Levels 3 and 4 unconstitutional and invalid. READ: Level 3 and Level 4 regulations declared unconstitutional Madonsela says although it is a great judgment, it lacked clarity, accuracy and persuasive reasoning. "It would have been best if the judgement had only specified which regulations are irrational and why," she said. WATCH: Law expert weighs in on lockdown judgment Government has noted the decision and has 14 days to respond. Level 3 regulations remain in operation for now. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.